ezvcard.property
Class Email

java.lang.Object
  ezvcard.property.VCardProperty
      ezvcard.property.SimpleProperty<String>
          ezvcard.property.TextProperty
              ezvcard.property.Email
All Implemented Interfaces:
HasAltId, Comparable<VCardProperty>
public class Email
extends TextProperty
implements HasAltId

Defines an email address associated with the person.

Code sample 

 VCard vcard = new VCard();
 
 Email email = new Email("johndoe@hotmail.com");
 email.addType(EmailType.HOME);
 vcard.addEmail(email);
 
 email = new Email("jdoe@company.com");
 email.addType(EmailType.WORK);
 email.setPref(1); //the most preferred email
 vcard.addEmail(email);

Property name: EMAIL

Supported versions: 2.1, 3.0, 4.0

Author:
Michael Angstadt

public Integer getPref()
Description copied from class: VCardProperty

Gets the preference value. The lower the number, the more preferred this property instance is compared with other properties in the same vCard of the same type. If a property doesn't have a preference value, then it is considered the least preferred.
